INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Developmental Disability, Alcoholism, Substance Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to the early intervention program
EventItemMatterName: Early intervention program.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of homeless services to post shelter census data
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the dept of homeless services to post shelter census data.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the operation of horse drawn cabs and pedicabs, and to repeal subdivision c of section 20-374 of the administrative code of the city of New York, relating to licenses for additional horse-drawn cabs
EventItemMatterName: Operation of horse drawn cabs and pedicabs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling for the establishment of a commission to study the potential creation of a national Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual and Transgender History Museum.
EventItemMatterName: Establishment of a commission to study the potential creation of a national Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual and Transgender History Museum.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State of New York to include in its curriculum requirements, swimming lessons and water safety education to all students in public schools from kindergarten through 12th grade where appropriate and swimming-related instruction, such as water safety and dry land strokes to all students in public schools from kindergarten through 12th grade when their school does not have a pool in the building or is not within 10 miles of a pool where appropriate.
EventItemMatterName: Include in its curriculum requirements, swimming lessons and water safety education to all students in public schools from kindergarten through 12th grade.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution declaring Youth Day in New York City, to be held annually each year on August 12th, coinciding with International Youth Day.
EventItemMatterName: Declaring Youth Day in NYC, to be held annually each year on August 12th, coinciding with International Youth Day.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation to ensure an equal number of employers and union representatives on the New York City Deferred Compensation Board.
EventItemMatterName: Ensure an equal number of employers and union representatives on the NYC Deferred Compensation Board.

EventItemActionText: This Land Use Application was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Application No. 20155248 HAM submitted by the New York City Department of Housing Preservation and Development pursuant to Section 577 of the Private Housing Finance Law for a real property tax exemption for properties located at 538-548 West 53rd Street (Block 1081, part of Lot 1), Borough of the Manhattan, Community Board 4, Council District 3.
EventItemMatterName: Planning, 538-548 West 53rd St, Manhattan (20155248 HAM)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring a universal mobile application to enable customers to electronically hail taxicabs and street hail livery vehicles.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring a universal mobile application to enable customers to electronically hail taxicabs and street hail livery vehicles.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring certain city contractors to implement workplace violence prevention programs.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring certain city contractors to implement workplace violence prevention programs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, A.2819, which would establish a hospitality gift fund for the homeless.
EventItemMatterName: Establish a hospitality gift fund for the homeless. (A.2819)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State of New York to match the City of New York’s commitment to create 15,000 units of supportive housing over 15 years, and the State of New York and the City of New York to approve a fourth “New York/New York Agreement” to create permanent supportive housing
EventItemMatterName: Approve a fourth “New York/New York Agreement” to create permanent supportive housing.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to speed limits in New York city parks.
EventItemMatterName: Speed limits in NYC parks.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the disclosure of information regarding buyout agreements.
EventItemMatterName: Disclosure of information regarding buyout agreements.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to limiting nighttime illumination for certain buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Limiting nighttime illumination for certain buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Public School Athletic League (PSAL) to provide a medical professional and an ambulance for High School Football games as well as practices in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Public School Athletic League (PSAL) to provide a medical professional and an ambulance for High School Football games as well as practices in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign, A.8763-A/S.7242 legislation that would establish a task force on arts and music education in elementary and secondary schools to study and make recommendations on the curriculum and funds spent on arts and music education in the New York State elementary and secondary school system.
EventItemMatterName: Establish a task force on arts and music education in elementary and secondary schools. (A.8763-A/S.7242)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to reporting on the racial and gender makeup of applicants for firefighter civil service examinations, and admission and graduation statistics from the probationary firefighter school.
EventItemMatterName: Reporting on the racial and gender makeup of applicants for firefighter civil service examinations, and admission and graduation statistics from the probationary firefighter school.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Economic Development
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to an infrastructure task force.
EventItemMatterName: Infrastructure task force.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to including 311 reports as official notice to the City of unsafe street or sidewalk conditions.
EventItemMatterName: Including 311 reports as official notice to the City of unsafe street or sidewalk conditions.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Aging
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to transferring administration of the senior citizen rent increase exemption (SCRIE) and disability rent increase exemption (DRIE) programs to the department of finance.
EventItemMatterName: Transferring administration of the SCRIE and DRIE programs to the dept of finance.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing e-mail and text message notifications regarding major transportation projects.
EventItemMatterName: Providing e-mail and text message notifications regarding major transportation projects.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring reporting on crime statistics in shelters.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring reporting on crime statistics in shelters.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution declaring January 15th - 22nd of each year as Peace Week in the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Declaring January 15th - 22nd of each year as Peace Week in NYC.
